<TITLE> Nassa Garments closed down over labour unrest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  The owners Wednesday closed a garment factory indefinitely in Dhaka in the wake of labour unrest, police said. Some of the workers of Nassa Garments found a notice of the shutdown in the morning when they came to work at the factory in Tejgaon industrial area. Tejgaon police chief Shafiqul Islam said security had been shored up in the area after the decision of the shutdown apprehending unrest. But no chaos had taken place there, he said by phone. Security officials had arrested some workers before Eid when they demonstrated to demand unpaid wages. The workers then demanded release of their detained colleagues. Most of the workers did not join the factory after Eid. The factory owners could not be reached for comment. bdnews2
